Swift Code (BIC)  - BARCCHGG XXX - BARCLAYS BANK (SUISSE) S.A.


























































Search by country
F.A.Q.
IFSC codes



What is a SWIFT code? A SWIFT code (or BIC code) is a unique code that identifies financial and non-financial institutions and is mainly used for international wire transfers between banks.














Swift Code (BIC)  - BARCCHGG XXX - BARCLAYS BANK (SUISSE) S.A.


          In this page you will find detailed information about the swift code “BARCCHGGXXX” of “BARCLAYS BANK (SUISSE) S.A.”.
        












              Institution
            

